<TEXT>
in an academic study of the air time 
television preachers devote to fundraising and promotion cited in 
an associated press article march 16 the findings for pat 
robertsons show were inflated by an overemphasis on special 
telethon programs 
the communications professor who conducted the study stephen 
winzenburg of des moines grand view college said robertson 
devoted an average 44 percent of air time to fundraising and 
promotion robertsons organization says its record shows that the 
robertson programs on average devote 18 percent of air time to what 
they regard as fundraising and promotion 
winzenburg says a disproportionate concentration of telethon 
programs among the robertson programs he monitored may have skewed 
the result two of the six robertson shows he studied were telethon 
programs 
winzenburg says the nontelethon robertson shows he monitored 
devoted an average 30 percent of air time to content he considered 
to be fundraising and promotion 
</TEXT>
