<TEXT>
its midmorning and publisher robert maxwell is 
on the telephone lambasting someone about distribution problems in 
germany or doing an interview with a london radio station 
its part of a hectic countdown to friday when the 66yearold 
tycoon launches his latest venture a paneuropean weekly 
fired by a vision of a united europe he says hell back the 
newspaper the european for as long as europe is around and 
rails against those skeptical about the viability of the european 
as uninformed biased scribblers 
with the crumbling of the eastwest divide in europe and moves 
toward closer unity of the 12nation european community maxwell 
believes the european is an idea whose time has come 
the europeans have ended their stupid nationalism he says 
were in the business of uniting europe 
there are no buts about this maxwell said in an interview 
in his penthouse suite at maxwell house london headquarters of a 
global publishing and communications empire spanning two dozen 
countries 
hes the new papers owner editorinchief masthead designer 
and owner of the company doing the color 
ive taken on the role of editorinchief for this newspaper 
because the europeans want to have a guarantee that this isnt just 
some perfidious albion foisting a european newspaper on the natives 
on the continent he told the london radio station 
and since im born in czechoslovakia speak a lot of european 
languages and everyone knows im more patriotic than the natives of 
this country im virtually tailormade for the job he said 
the 64page englishlanguage newspaper will have an initial 
print run of 1 million copies friday selling in london for 84 
cents each half in color it has three sections main news 
business and sports and a 32page tabloid lifestyle and arts 
section called elan 
the theater listings include whats on from amsterdam to zagreb 
via cluj romania a dummy edition has frontpage stories about 
europe from moscow berlin and paris and inside are congratulatory 
letters from among others polands lech walesa and anglofrench 
actress charlotte rampling 
actor peter ustinov writes a column and the editorial staff of 
100 includes some top names in european journalism the paper is 
being printed in london frankfurt roubaix in france and near 
budapest in hungary 
maxwell britains secondbiggest newspaper publisher after 
rupert murdoch is launching the european as part of the mirror 
group newspapers which he bought in 1984 
he says he is spending 41 million on the europeans launch and 
guarantees advertisers sales of 225000 copies weekly from july to 
december 60 percent in britain if sales are under 225000 
advertisers get rebates the breakeven point maxwell says is 
300000 
the european enters a british market which with 21 national 
daily and sunday newspapers has never been more crowded 
the boom results chiefly from the defeat of the printworkers 
unions which were crushed by murdoch and maxwell to usher in the 
high technology on which the european depends 
media analysts credit maxwell with a brave new idea 
but many question whether the european is viable only in english 
and with twothirds of its projected sales in britain whether it 
can compete with established englishlanguage papers in europe 
such as the international herald tribune the wall street journal 
europe and the financial times and whether it can attract vital 
corporate advertising 
and the question remains whether there are enough dedicated 
europeans 
its an admirable and rather heroic idea says eric de 
bellaigue publishing analyst at the london brokerage panmure 
gordon but i would doubt if an awful lot of people are going to 
see themselves at this stage as being european and identifying 
automatically with something called the european 
its a very good product in search of a market says alec 
kenny media director of saatchi and saatchi advertising 
but you just have to wonder if there are enough people out 
there in the market place who really want this sort of product 
kenny said in an interview 
raymond snoddy media correspondent of the financial times 
agrees 
as a purely financial venture i wouldnt give many chances for 
the europeans longevity snoddy says but maxwell is committed 
to making it a success and he might be prepared to back it 
financially long enough until the perceptions of europeans catch up 
with his 
maxwell born labji hoch to jewish peasant parents who died at 
the hands of the nazis arrived in britain penniless in 1940 
a decorated world war ii british officer he has sat in 
parliament for the labor party but he has never quite been 
accepted by the british establishment and rival publications mock 
him as the bouncing czech and a selfpublicist 
in 1987 in a blaze of publicity maxwell launched a new british 
daily the london daily news which folded after five months but 
with the european maxwell insists hell spend anything for it to 
succeed 
mirror group newspapers makes a profit of 15 million a 
week he says i suspect they will be able to sustain any 
losses on the european for as long as europe is around 
</TEXT>
