kennedys advisers expected the worst from west virginia about 
90 percent protestant at the time although kennedy had won five of 
nine earlier primaries 
kennedy beat humphrey in west virginia 236510 votes to 152187 
although the vote made political history west virginias people 
and the grinding inescapable poverty some of them lived in made a 
lasting impression on the scion of a wealthy massachusetts family 
he had seen poverty before sorensen said but the 
longterm hardship faced by many of the people he met in west 
virginia the look on their face and the stories they told made a 
very deep impression on him it wasnt a theory any longer 
