follow the laws of war in refusing to free war prisoners upon the 
cessation of hostilities 
as for noriegas forces the report said they violated 
international law by taking civilian hostages and by dressing as 
civilians during the fighting thus attracting fire and exposing 
innocent people to combat 
the study also said the us southern command in panama 
undercounted the number of civilian deaths that resulted from the 
fighting the pentagon total was 202 but the report said 300 is 
more likely the real figure 
