subcommittee on oceanography and great lakes 
many states including new york and massachusetts have 
adopted epas swimmer health risk goal as their own with the 
result that many beaches deemed safe for swimming may actually be 
laced with sufficient pathogens to make hundreds of people each day 
sick with gastroenteritis and other diseases 
cameron said a zero health risk is achievable because it doesnt 
mean zero pathogens she also suggested developing a bathing 
