onethird of the public had focused intense interest on an 
individual news event the survey said 
political change in eastern and central europe earlier had been 
the most consistently watched story generating interest among 
about 30 percent of respondents since september the survey found 
the second most popular story in april was the celebration of 
earth day which 31 percent of respondents said they watched 
closely 
