the nations no 1 supplier of 
laboratory mice says it is up to 70 percent capacity after a fire 
one year ago today that dealt a blow to medical research projects 
around the world 
the blaze at jackson laboratory killed 400000 mice and 
destroyed much of the 29yearold breeding complex now it is 
counting on at least 10 million from the national institutes of 
health for a full recovery 
well be at 85 percent by the end of this summer and well be 
at 100 percent by the end of 1991 if we get the 10 million from 
nih said director kenneth paigen who was about to assume the 
post when the fire broke out 
