hikes and measures to ease consumer shortages in an apparent 
attempt to boost the chances of the ruling former communist party 
in next months free elections 
lukanov told a news conference wednesday that minimum monthly 
wages will be raised as of june 1 the export of foodstuffs and 
other goods in short supply will be banned and a steep hard 
currency tax on imported cars will be abolished 
the government which recently suspended payments on bulgarias 
10 billion foreign debt also will try to import food and will 
guarantee the jobs of workers at unprofitable companies until after 
the elections lukanov said 
