democracy the communists remain in full control in bulgaria prior 
to the elections scheduled for june 10 
 
the premier a leading figure in the renamed communist party 
now the socialists said minimum monthly wages would be raised june 
1 from 140 to 170 leva under the current official exchange rate 
there are eight to nine leva to the dollar 
