angola is one of six socalled frontline states opposed to the 
apartheid system of whiteminority rule in south africa after 
independence from portugal in 1975 the marxist leaders allowed the 
anc to operate bases in angola 
since 1975 the rebel national union for the total independence 
of angola has fought a civil war in a bid to share power the 
group known as unita was formerly supported by south africa 
but under a 1988 regional peace accord south africa agreed to 
end aid to unita and granted independence to angolas southern 
neighbor namibia cuba also agreed to withdraw troops backing the 
angolan government 
