community is going to have to support it somehow 
this is a town willing to take a risk said mayor idella 
frickey it is a town that gets things done and i think well 
get this thing done too 
in a time when many small farming communities are struggling 
this town nestled in the shortgrass prairie 380 miles west of 
kansas city and 230 miles east of denver appears to be thriving 
the red brick streets wind through a town with a strong business 
community and several new homes a 25 million renovation of the 
hospital and nursing home was recently completed 
the city also runs its own carnival and theater local investors 
have helped start private enterprises such as boat and bus 
factories 
frickey says she is sure conflicts will arise over plans for the 
building but she and fear acknowledge it is a pleasant burden 
how many small towns in this part of the country wouldnt like 
to have a 1 million gift fear asked were sure not going to 
give it up without a fight 
