britains prince charles and princess 
diana on thursday ended their first visit to a warsaw pact country 
by viewing budapest from a boat on the danube and taking a 
streetcar ride through the city center 
the royal couple delighted hungarians and made frontpage news 
during a speech tuesday charles was full of praise for hungarys 
pioneering role in eastern europes transformation his wife drew 
admiration for her charm her smiles and her elegant clothes 
about 2000 people crowded a square adjoining the danube to 
greet the prince and princess after their streetcar ride costumed 
folk dancers delivered a traditional sendoff 
after so many hard years only now that i see them here on the 
streets of budapest and see everyone freely expressing their 
enthusiasm do i really believe that things have changed said 
emilia imredi a 68yearold pensioner 
</TEXT>
