<TEXT>
a man flying to florida to visit his mother 
in a nursing home landed in court for slugging the airline pilot 
after being told he was too tipsy for another drink authorities 
said 
lonnie alton lee 50 a lawn and pest control worker from 
albuquerque nm has been charged with endangering a commercial 
flight a federal offense punishable by up to 20 years in prison 
lee was en route to haines city on tuesday night for a surprise 
mothers day visit he was released on a 10000 signature bond 
during an appearance wednesday before a us magistrate in tampa 
donald t woods was piloting continental airlines flight 528 
from denver to orlando when the incident occurred somewhere over 
alabama 
a flight attendant refused to serve lee any more drinks because 
he was tipsy and had become belligerent authorities said 
lee began hurling obscenities at the male flight attendant then 
punched woods in the jaw when he tried to intervene said fbi 
spokesman larry curtin 
lee was restrained strapped into his seat until the plane 
landed and was arrested curtin said 
woods told federal agents the blow endangered the flight because 
he wore glasses and the swing could have shattered them or 
otherwise impaired his vision 
after asking authorities not to call his mother about the 
arrest lee told the magistrate he might just skip the holiday 
visit and return home 
