<TEXT>
rival christian forces under gen michel 
aoun and militia chieftain samir geagea exchanged artillery and 
tank barrages in east beirut on thursday shattering a relative 
lull in the fighting 
police said four people were killed and eight wounded in the 
heavy barrages that erupted after a day of intermittent skirmishes 
with machine guns and mortars 
it was the 101st day of the inconclusive showdown between aoun 
and geagea for control of the 310squaremile christian enclave 
a daytime lull gave the exhausted population a chance to emerge 
from underground shelters to take stock of damage from the savage 
shelling of the previous two days 
but residents quickly scurried back to their shelters when the 
heavy shelling resumed 
the casualties included a moslem driver whose vegetable van took 
a direct hit from a shell hit at the midcity museum gateway that 
links east beirut with the citys moslem sector across the dividing 
green line 
the gateway was opened only minutes before being closed again 
police said 
the aoungeagea fight has killed 980 people and wounded 2572 
since it erupted jan 30 
the guns generally fell silent by midnight wednesday a police 
spokesman said but snipers manning rooftop firing nests kept most 
roads blocked in east beirut and the christian enclave northeast of 
the city 
snipers also targeted the museum gateway and few civilians 
ventured across the dividing line 
the crackle of automatic fire echoed across the museum gateway 
as a woman and three men sped on foot toward west beirut hurry 
up keep your heads down shouted a moslem soldier on the western 
side 
the four made it safely across and said they were going to stay 
with relatives 
the woman janette elia said the street where she had lived in 
furn elshubbak district was reduced to mere piles of rubble 
debris and glass shards 
geageas men fired salvo after salvo of rockets from 
multibarrelled launchers at our street mrs elia said the 
rockets came in like endless sea waves whistling and exploding 
mrs elia said she spent the whole day and night wednesday in 
the basement of her home most of the residents had already fled 
to safer areas she said 
the fighting has forced 400000 of the enclaves 1 million 
residents to flee to safer areas in lebanon and neighboring 
countries and inflicted damage estimated at 1 billion 
aouns troops and geageas fighters also used the lull to defuse 
scores of unexploded shells and rockets remove the rubble that 
blocked some streets and resupply their positions with food water 
and ammunition a police spokesman said 
they are preparing for another round of destruction the 
spokesman said the reason for the clash is still there and the 
weapons are still there theyll fight again 
the fierce shelling was apparently halted by a ceasefire call 
from maronite patriarch nasrallah sfeir both aoun and geagea are 
maronites too 
the violence had escalated wednesday when aoun imposed 
restrictions on sea outlets controlled by geagea along the 28mile 
christian coastline 
