<TEXT>
premier andrei lukanov said thursday he 
is prepared to head bulgarias next government even if his 
socialist party the former communist party is defeated in 
elections next month and forced into a coalition with the 
opposition 
the socialist party seeks a firm break with its stalinist past 
lukanov said in an interview with the associated press 
the party which changed its name last month is now dominated 
by those who want a new european socialist party who are 
resolutely antistalinist lukanov said 
bulgarias communist party draws on almost a century of 
tradition in the months immediately following novembers ouster of 
todor zhivkov after 35 years in power it retained stronger 
standing than any other communist party in eastern europe 
but the democratic opposition while still splintered has 
gained ground and is approaching the elections june 10 and 17 with 
confidence 
petko simeonov a leading opposition figure predicted tuesday 
that the newly named socialists would suffer a catastrophic 
defeat at the polls 
but lukanov an economist who is well respected by all political 
groups in bulgaria maintained the socialists will emerge as the 
strongest political force after the elections 
he stopped short of predicting a majority for bulgarias 
erstwhile communists in view of the recent electoral defeat of 
hungarys socialists who guided their country to peaceful reform 
asked if he would be willing to head a government if the 
socialists do not emerge victorious lukanov replied if the 
party considers this the right thing to do i would not have a 
personal position on it and would take the job 
but he later added this prospect does not make me happy 
several leaders of the opposition union of democratic forces say 
they would like to see the savvy lukanov stay at the helm in a 
coalition 
a coalition is necessary whoever wins we need at least for 
a transitory period a government enjoying if not 100 percent 
very massive public support lukanov said 
the political economic and legal reforms ahead of us are of 
such a magnitude of such complexity that we do not think it 
possible for anyone in a single political force to shoulder this 
he added 
 
