<TEXT>
eugene long has enjoyed a reputation as the 
city where the peace crusade of the 1960s did not die so it wasnt 
surprising that voters declared it a nuclear free zone in 1986 
but as oregon struggles to diversify its economy to make up for 
the decline of the timber industry residents are confronted with 
paying a price for their convictions on tuesday they will decide 
whether to toughen the ordinance that bans the local manufacture of 
nuclear weapons and their components 
although eugene population 110000 is in many ways a timber 
town the presence of the 18500student university of oregon has 
given it a liberal tone not found elsewhere in oregon 
but the proposed city charter amendment has scared away the 
builders of a 15 million factory one small defense contractor 
vows to move out of the city if the nuclear free zone measure 
passes 
rohr industries earlier this year decided to build a new jet 
engine parts plant in san marcos texas rather than eugene with 
it went 250 jobs 
eugene had made the short list said jerry broening 
director of public affairs for rohr in san diego indeed we had 
selected eugene tentatively to locate the facility 
then it came to our notice that there was this pending 
stiffening of the existing nuclear free zone ordinance in eugene 
supporters launched the latest initiative after the city council 
and a special task force refused to establish an elected board to 
oversee the nuclear free zones approved by voters in 1986 and 1988 
the latest initiative would amend the city charter keeping the 
council out of the process 
a nuclearfree zone in oakland calif was declared 
unconstitutional last month in the federal governments first 
lawsuit against a such a law a federal judge said the ordinance 
interfered with exclusive federal control of national defense 
atomic energy and shipments of hazardous materials 
steve johnson the chief petitioner for the initiative to make 
the nuclear free zone part of the city charter said the oakland 
case shouldnt affect the his proposal because it does not attempt 
to directly limit decisions by the federal and state governments 
as oaklands did 
and while eugenes measure would prohibit hauling nuclear wastes 
over city streets it doesnt try to stop passage on interstate 5 
or the railroad johnson said 
johnson an adjunct sociology professor at the university of 
oregon calls the initiative a chance to force the city council to 
finally accept the will of the people as expressed in the previous 
nuclearfree votes i thought the voters got a rotten deal he 
said 
but mike schwartz cochairman of citizens against an 
irresponsible nuclear free zone said the vote is really about 
whether people want to see their economy grow 
this is camouflage that people who dont want growth are 
using said schwartz 
though nuclear free zone advocates say rohr wouldnt have been 
covered by the ballot measure broening said the company didnt 
want its future restricted in any way besides it was in a hurry 
to build its plant 
we are a subcontractor and our customers ask us to do things 
and if they ask us to do things we respond broening said we 
needed to have a plant in operation by october which was patently 
undoable if we had to wait until june for the outcome of the 
vote 
robert ellis is president of biodynamics a 10yearold eugene 
defense contractor that employs 25 people to make flight simulators 
and handle secret military projects 
ellis finds the local climate so hostile to his company that he 
plans to move it if the new nuclear free zone passes 
its 1969 in eugene he said for our children there is no 
good potential employment in eugene oregon unless you want to 
make belts 
david zupan a staffer for the organization peaceworks who is 
active on the nuclear free zone campaign figures rohrs decision 
should encourage people that the new improved nuclear free zone 
will work 
they should be relieved that a company that wants to make 
nuclear weapons is not coming to eugene zupan said 
the impression was that rohr would employ outofwork mill 
workers johnson said the fact is these are people they bring 
with them or attract from outside the area we dont have a big 
pool with specialty metal fabrication experience 
