systems guaranteed share of the federal market 
coble said furniture and textile companies in north carolina are 
hurt by the burgeoning prison manufacturing program which sold 240 
different products to federal agencies last year the sales totaled 
361 million and are expected to double by 1992 the program 
employed 13000 inmates and 1400 civilians 
