residents of wisconsin illinois and michigan residents traded 
swimsuits and garden hoes for parkas and snow shovels thursday as 
freak storm brought back winter in may 
the spring shocker was worst in wisconsin where snowfall up to 
8 inches shattered records for late season snow 
some communities had to reassemble snowplows that had been 
stored for the season residents who broke out the lawn furniture 
and headed for the beach when tempeatures reached the 70s and 80s 
just two days before dug their coats out of mothballs 
we expect anything up here said police officer ron 
