mph was blamed for hundreds of accidents and two traffic deaths 
powerlines downed by wind or accumulated ice caused temporary 
blackouts in more than 40000 homes 
the storm was caused by a lowpressure system that sucked cold 
air down from canada and moisture up from the south according to 
the national weather service 
weather service specialist edmond lowe said the snowfall while 
not the latest in wisconsin history was a record for spring 
surpassing the 5 inches recorded april 30 1907 the latest snow 
ever to fall in spring in wisconsin was may 31 1889 
