<TEXT>
congressional backers of a proposal to 
standardize state productliability laws charged thursday that 
consumer groups have tried to thwart the legislation through a 
campaign to trash anybody who stands in their way 
the legislation backed by the bush administration and business 
representatives would create a uniform federal standard for 
imposing punitive damages in lawsuits involving products that cause 
death or serious injury 
consumer groups have said the bill would unduly limit peoples 
ability to collect for deaths and injuries that result from 
industry negligence or irresponsibility 
backers of the legislation argue that variations in liability 
laws from state to state offer potentially limitless damages and 
hinder product development and american competitiveness 
the accusations against consumer groups came as linda lipsen 
legislative counselor for consumers union outlined what she said 
were misrepresentations given at previous hearings by the senate 
commerce committees consumer subcommittee into the safety of a 
nevermarketed substitute for asbestos that was manufactured by the 
missouribased monsanto co 
the administration and the manufacturing community have 
asserted before you that the product liability system prevented a 
totally safe substitute for asbestos calcium sodium metaphosphate 
from being marketed said lipsen beginning her testimony 
before the panel 
sen john danforth rmo interrupted lipsen noting that she 
had not included her comments about monsanto or its product in the 
21page written testimony she submitted to the panel for review 
before thursdays hearing 
i think you wanted to catch people unawares said danforth 
it is a sneak attack it is a sneaky sneaky move on your part 
he added to the applause of many spectators 
lipsen responded it is not our normal course of business to 
impugn even indirectly members of this administration or 
witnesses before you 
lipsen was speaking on behalf of four organizations cu the 
consumer federation of america public citizen and the public 
interest research group 
the last two groups were founded by noted consumer advocate 
ralph nader consumers union is the nonprofit membership group that 
publishes consumer reports magazine 
asbestos is a fireretardant fiber that was used widely in 
building construction until it was found to cause cancer 
i think this is very typical of the nader organizations to 
trash people trash politicians trash businesses trash anybody 
who stands in their way added danforth 
nader who was not present at the hearing was again mentioned 
by sen jay rockefeller dwva who angrily noted an open letter 
to him from the consumer advocate the letter which questioned 
rockefellers integrity was sent to newspapers in west virginia 
according to rockefeller naders letter asked why are you 
spending your time huddled in washington with corporate lobbyists 
many of whom finance your campaign gambling with the lives and 
safety of millions of people by taking away rights to seek relief 
by supporting federal product liability law 
completing her statement lipsen told the panel it had not been 
informed in previous testimony about a 1986 review by the 
environmental protection agency that said there was reason to 
believe the asbestos substitute also could be carcinogenic 
the bill would place a twoyear limit on most product liability 
claims with the exception of a 25year limit on workers injury 
claims 
the measure also would allow separate trials or settlements of 
damage claims when a suit involves more than one company firms 
would pay damages in proportion of their responsibility for harm 
the legislation would exempt from punitive damages manufacturers 
whose products had received premarket approval from the food and 
drug administration or the federal aviation administration 
asked later about the charges levied by backers of the bill 
nader dismissed the criticisms as a side show designed to 
distract attention from key liability issues 
these senators dont want to concentrate on explaining why 
they are siding with the corporations that are producing deadly 
toxic materials that are killing and injuring hundreds of thousands 
of americans a year he said 
furthermore they dont want to answer the question to 
document the reason for their supporting this wall street 
legislation with specific numbers nader added 
