<TEXT>
two juries in the bensonhurst racial slaying 
deliberated a second day without a verdict thursday as police in 
riot gear stood guard at the courthouse where demonstrators 
attacked a defense attorney a day earlier 
separate state supreme court juries are considering the cases 
against alleged gang leader keith mondello and accused gunman 
joseph fama both 19 
the defendants both white are charged with seconddegree 
murder and other crimes in the aug 23 slaying of 16yearold yusuf 
hawkins who was black each faces 25 years to life if convicted of 
murder 
rain sent demonstrators in the courthouse square scurrying for 
cover and their cardboard placards became sodden and smeared a 
police officer on the scene said 100 protesters gathered in the 
square at one point thursday but virtually no one remained by late 
afternoon 
on wednesday mondellos attorney stephen murphy was punched 
in the face by one of about 300 protesters demanding murder 
convictions in the case 
when murphy took a lunch break thursday he was surrounded 
briefly by a handful of protesters shouting yusuf yusuf but 
he returned to the courthouse without incident 
lines of blue police barricades were erected in front of the 
courthouse and more than 50 police officers many in riot gear 
were on hand 
inside jurors considering the charges against mondello and fama 
continued to rehear trial testimony and to reexamine evidence 
thursday was the third full day of deliberations for the fama jury 
and the second full day for the mondello panel 
both juries went home for the night thursday without reaching 
verdicts 
prosecutors allege mondello organized a mob of batcarrying 
whites who surrounded hawkins and his three companions all black 
fama allegedly stepped from the mob and fatally shot hawkins in the 
chest with a 32 caliber automatic 
justice thaddeus owens said the juries which are sequestered 
during deliberations would work through the weekend if they fail 
to reach a verdict earlier 
