<TEXT>
the former president of a manila bank testified 
in imelda marcos fraud trial thursday that millions of dollars 
from accounts secretly held by the marcoses were used to buy 
manhattan real estate 
rolando gapud a key government witness said he personally 
managed a series of numbered accounts at his bank security bank 
and trust co for mrs marcos and her husband former philippine 
president ferdinand e marcos 
gapud said marcos had secretly acquired control of the bank in 
1980 and ordered the opening of the accounts a year later 
gapud testified that between 1982 and 1985 he transferred 50 
to 60 million from the accounts for the purchase and maintenance 
of four new york buildings 40 wall st the crown building at 730 
fifth ave herald center and 200 madison ave 
the transfers were made on the instructions of mrs marcos 
personal secretary fe roa jimenez gapud said 
mrs marcos is accused of helping her late husband loot their 
nations treasury of more than 220 million to secretly buy the new 
york properties identified by gapud 
she has pleaded innocent to charges of racketeering 
racketeering conspiracy mail fraud and obstruction of justice 
her codefendant saudi businessman adnan khashoggi is charged 
with mail fraud and obstruction of justice for allegedly helping 
the marcoses hide their ownership of the four buildings and artwork 
gapud described the complicated process by which the marcoses 
involvement in the transactions was kept confidential 
he said the accounts at his bank which all had 7700 
numbers were opened through other numbered accounts at a hong kong 
bank that were secretly held by the marcoses 
the money transferred from the security bank accounts went to 
corporations controlled by the marcoses which were used to buy the 
buildings gapud said 
the banker also told of the means by which the marcoses bypassed 
philippine central bank regulations that limited the amount of us 
dollars allowed out of the country 
in one scheme gapud said he and geronimo velasco marcos 
former minister of energy arranged to have the dollar profits from 
exports of the governmentowned philippine national oil company 
deposited into marcos bank accounts in the united states 
the oil company was reimbursed with the equivalent in philippine 
pesos from the 7700 accounts at security bank and trust co 
gapud said 
these transactions took place between october 1982 and the 
spring of 1983 and involved 70 million he said part of the money 
was used toward the purchase of 40 wall st in december 1982 he 
said 
gapud said philippine businessmen also were asked to submit 
phony applications to the central bank for approval to transfer 
dollars from the philippines 
in two instances one involving a 30 million transfer and 
another 8 million gapud said the businessmen were acting as 
fronts for marcos who gave them pesos from the 7700 accounts 
to pay for the us dollars 
