<TEXT>
pope john paul ii on thursday 
criticized populous mexicos family planning program called for 
freedom of religious education and demanded greater parental input 
on sex education in public schools 
john paul backed roman catholic parents groups pressing for 
religious education he said they have the right to freely 
educate their children according to their own religious 
convictions and to have the laws of their country explicitly 
recognize that right 
religious schools are constitutionally prohibited in mexico 
although many exist and are tolerated despite the ban religious 
education would probably expand quickly if the ban were lifted 
however 
the pontiff noted in a speech before more than 100000 people 
that educational freedom is a right recognized by the universal 
declaration of human rights even though serious legislative 
limits still exist in some countries 
it was the fifth day of the pontiffs eightday mexican journey 
the crowd included thousands of us residents who traveled by bus 
and car to chihuahua 220 miles south of el paso texas 
the pontiff spoke from a platform on a dusty field with the 
bare brown sierra madre mountains in the background thousands in 
the audience waved flags in vatican yellow and white many wore 
straw hats and caps 
the sunny day was marred by word that a plane carrying pilgrims 
crashed near tuxtla gutierrez more than 1000 miles away in 
southeastern mexico the pope visits tuxtla gutierrez on friday 
more than two dozen were reported dead in the crash including the 
bishop of tapachula luis miguel canton marin 
may god grant the dead eternal rest and a rapid recovery to 
the injured john paul said thursday evening in the northern 
industrialized city of monterrey in a brief comment on the 
accident he spoke before a crowd there estimated at more than 
500000 by far the largest of the trip 
the pope changed his friday schedule and will visit the 
cathedral in tuxtla gutierrez to pray for the victims and offer 
condolences to their families 
in his homily at a mass dedicated to workers the pontiff again 
condemned the materialism of the capitalist system 
without denying the good results obtained where a free 
system reigns we still cannot be blinded to the defects of an 
economic system that not infrequently makes riches and consumption 
its principle engine he said 
monterrey mexicos thirdlargest city is less than 100 miles 
from laredo texas and the crowd included thousands of us 
residents the service took place in the dry bed of the santa 
catarina river 
at chihuahua the pope reiterated the churchs opposition to 
artificial contraceptives 
if in the conjugal union the possibility of conceiving a 
child is artificially eliminated the couple closed themselves to 
god and opposed his will john paul said 
the standard church message has political implications in 
mexico where since the mid1970s the government has encouraged use 
of contraceptives to limit a mushrooming population government 
health clinics distribute contraceptives and perform vasectomies 
but abortion is illegal 
the program one of the most succesful in the third world has 
helped cut the population growth rate from nearly 37 percent in 
1977 to 19 percent according to government figures 
nearly half the married women in this overwhelmingly catholic 
country use contraceptives according to international planned 
parenthood figures still the population has increased nearly 30 
percent reaching 85 million since john paul first visited in 
1979 
strong religious restrictions were written into the 1917 
constitution after liberals defeated churchbacked conservatives 
during the mexican revolution 
the pope said that by using birth control a husband and wife 
closed themselves to each other in that they reject the mutual 
giving in paternity and maternity reducing the conjugal union to 
an occasion for satisfying the egoism of each one 
the papal position has drawn fire in mexico where infant 
mortality illiteracy and malnutrition are major problems 
john paul also said sex education that ignores moral values 
constitutes an impoverishment of the person and contributes to 
obscuring his dignity 
the pope attacked elements he said violated the human rights of 
children including abortion malnutrition lack of affection 
violence and drugs 
he also paid a mothers day tribute to mexican women mothers 
day is celebrated on may 10 in latin america 
